                                                      July 19, 2023\par
    A new version of VirtualU is available for download because changes were made to it. We are sorry that it took longer than expected to get this version ready but it is worth the wait.          \par
    *Improvement made: The text of the Custom page Project menu item tool "Show location of extracted movie frames" has been changed to "Show location and thumbnails of extracted frames". This tool now shows the location and the actual thumbnail images of the frames extracted from a selected video.\par
    *Bug found: In previous versions if a video is rotated, followed by some other image-altering tool, followed by a cancellation of the second image-altering tool then the video would most likely not return to its correct original width and height if the video is dragged and released. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *Improvement made: The tool "Use eraser or do hand/auto draw" in the Transparencies menu on the Custom page would formerly only accept BMPs. It now accepts BMPs, JPGs, PNGs and GIfs.\par
    *Oversight corrected: Previous versions would sometimes erroneously allow multiple user prompts to be open at the same time, which could lead to problems. This has been corrected.\par
    *Improvement made: The Capture Image button on the Custom page no longer requires any automatic tests to be run in order that the Capture Image process receive settings data. In other words, the Capture Image button may be pressed at any time without anything else being done prior to that.\par
    *New tool: A new tool titled Outline on the contrast/hue/lum/sat page enables a user to create a transparency by drawing lines and curves around foreground images in pictures and videos. Lines and curves can be drawn around foreground images by means of bezier curves and straight lines that can be quickly drawn at any angle and length without needing to use freehand drawing, though this page also offers freehand drawing. For videos the outlines can be drawn one frame at a time or applied to all the frames at once. After the outlines are drawn then everything either outside or inside the outlines can be filled with a solid color using floodfill System 2 on the contrast/hue/lum/sat page. Later the solid color can be made transparent so that the foreground images can then be edge softened to any background, not just the original background. This tool is designed for picture and video images in which the background and foreground images are both not composed of solid colors. See the June 23 log report for illustrated examples of how the many tools on the Outline page work. This tool can also remove any existing edge softening from pictures and videos.\par
    *New menu item: A new menu item titled "Misc-Machines\\How To Make A Transparency - System 2" has been added to the Custom page. This instruction page uses text and illustrations to explain how to use the new Outline tool.\par
    *Bug found: The tool "Tools\\Create movie from frames" on the Custom page can only make AVI movies from BMP frames. When we erroneously attempted to use this tool to make an AVI from PNG frames, the program displayed an error message and we discovered that the "Load 1st Frame And Movie Name" button was incorrectly disabled. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *Improvements made: Certain tools on the Outline page enable the user to save and load outline drawings to picture files that contain the reproduced shapes of the drawings. The user can load these shapes and position them over the picture or video image. This capability can speed things up by removing the need to redraw curves and lines. These shapes can also be rotated and flipped horizontally or vertically. The cropping tool on the Outline page can automatically crop out all the blank space around any foreground image/s on shape pictures, making loaded shapes more manageable and easier to work with. The cropping tool can crop any image that has a solid color background so it can have extensive applications outside of the Outline page. The user can opt to have the endpoints of lines and curves snap together and the Outline page offers many other tools.\par
    *Problem found: Some processes use the same form to display different user messages and prompts. If one process was using a particular form to display a message, previous versions would erroneously allow the user to start a different process that uses the same form and this could lead to problems. We have taken steps to ensure that these problems do not happen.\par
    *Improvement made: When the user increases the display scale setting then the maximum available capture width and height are reduced. If the maximum capture size is less than the current capture size setting then automatic cropping will occur. In such cases the program now will alert the user to this fact before any captures or recordings are made and the program will advise the user to temporarily reduce the scale, do the capture or recording and then if desired increase the scale back to the larger size. In such cases the program will also make other suggestions.\par
    *Future plans: We have some other projects coming up in August and September but as soon as possible we plan to enable the Outline page to create polygons and other custom drawings and shapes with adjustable hinges/nodes/joints. These shapes would be prevented from being automatically deleted when altering a video frame by frame so that they can be repeatedly used and if necessary reshaped for each frame.\par
    Special thanks to the Lazarus Forum which provided very valuable help. Re: wp (Forum member)\par
    The current download version of VirtualU contains the changes mentioned above.\par
