                                                     August 1, 2023\par
    A new version of VirtualU is available for download because changes were made to it and new tools have been added.\par
    *Improvement made: The Rotation page only does counter clockwise rotation for videos that require counter clockwise progressive (continuous frame by frame) rotation but that page now has a new tool that calculates the number of positive clockwise degrees needed to achieve a given counter clockwise rotation.\par
    *New tool: The Outline page which makes outlines of foreground images in order to remove the existing backgrounds around those foreground images has a new custom tool that makes adjustable polygons (multi-sided, mulit-jointed outline shapes). Each joint of the custom polygon is movable and the user can add or remove joints as needed.\par
    *Correction made: The Playback/Recording page is supposed to load even if a color sample box is showing if the user so desires but the previous version didn't allow that. This has been corrected.\par
    *Improvements made: Miscellaneous improvements were made throughout the program. Among other things, these improvements help insure that no problems occur if an attempt is made to start a process while another process is already running. User prompts have also been changed to reflect recent changes.\par
    *The tool "Image\\Change image color to solid color" on the Custom page previously would only work with BMPs. This tool now accepts all formats including BMP, JPG, GIF and PNG.\par
    *Current activities and future plans: We are currently exploring the possibility of creating an Outline page tool that will by itself draw an outline around foreground images by means of a semi-automatic method using edge detection techniques. We do not yet know if this will be feasible but it appears that it may work. If it does work then it will be a real game changer. Such a tool should work in most cases and it would tremendously speed up the outlining process and make the task much easier for the user.\par
    The current download version of VirtualU contains the changes mentioned above.\par
\par
                                                        August 21, 2023\par
    A new version of VirtualU is available for download because changes were made to it and a new tool has been added.\par
    *Bug found: The options on the Outline page that change the colors of a polygon joint and its background did not always work correctly in previous versions. This has been fixed.\par
    *New tool: A new tool titled "Auto Outline\\Run Auto Outline System 1" on the Outline page makes a transparency out of a picture or video that contains a non-solid color foreground image superimposed over a semi-solid color background or backdrop. For example, if a person takes a picture of himself or herself positioned in front of a sheet or backdrop of some kind, this tool will ensure that the background will go transparent so that the person can then superimpose his or her image over some new, completely different background. The background in Fig. 1 below shows a multi-colored bowl suspended in front of a red sheet background. That background is imperfect and will not go transparent until it is altered with the System 1 tool and then the de-edging tool as shown in Fig. 3. The bowl in Fig. 3 which now has raster scan hard edges may be superimposed and edge softened to any new solid or multi-colored background that is different than the original background.\par
    *Bug found: When "Tools\\Convert to a new frame rate w/same playback speed/duration" on the Custom page is selected then at some point the program will prompt the user to enter a frame rate and press the GO button but when we ran this tool we discovered that the GO button erroneously did not appear. This bug has been fixed.\par
     *Current activities: We are currently working on a new transparency system that will be titled "Auto Outline System 2" and it will hopefully be available in the next version. This system will remove the background shown in Fig. 2 and will also produce the image shown in Fig. 3. Of course the graphics industry does provide costly programs that do this kind of very challenging process but we think that we can do better. This new tool should be able to successfully alter most pictures and videos as long as they contain foreground images that are at least reasonably different than their backgrounds. This tool will require some quick minor preparatory work by the user but the tedious and time consuming work of using the manual outline tools can in many cases be avoided with the aid of this fast and easy tool.\par
    *We have tested the new Auto Outline System 1 tool extensively and will continue testing it. If we find any issues then we will fix them and report them.\par
    The current download version of VirtualU contains the changes mentioned above.\par
