\par
                                                                         September 9, 2023\par
     This is an update. No new version of VirtualU is available at this time.\par
     We are currently involved with a project other than VirtualU but yet we are also finding time to work on a new VirtualU tool. We are about to conduct some tests that will prove or disprove that tool's capability to remove multi-colored backgrounds from pictures or videos that contain a multi-colored foreground image which needs to be outlined.     \par
     The kind of image that we are talking about is shown in the picture Fig. 2 which is attached to the previous August 21 log report. In terms of removing backgrounds, this kind of f.g. image is extremely difficult to successfully process.\par
     This tool will have some limitations and restrictions but hopefully it will still be able to automatically handle most though perhaps not all foreground images. For example, some pictures or video frames may require the user to apply the available manual tools to some images.\par
     In any event, this tool should considerably speed up and simplify the outlining process. If our efforts are successful then this tool will become the capstone and crowning achievement of VirtualU.\par
     We will report the results of these tests as soon as possible.\par
\par
                                                                        November 1, 2023\par
This is an update.\par
     We continue to work on the new Auto Outline System 2 tool when we can but for the most part we have been involved with other things. We think that our preliminary design is capable of producing a useful tool and we hope to eventually pick up the pace and get more done. We will keep you advised and not allow so much time to elapse between updates. Thank you very much.\par
\par
                                                                          December 8, 2023\par
     This is an update. Providence willing and as described previously in this document, we are pleased to report that a future version of VirtualU will contain a new semi-automatic tool on the Outline page which will enable the user to change the background of a picture or video image while leaving forground images intact. This tool is called Auto Outline System 2.  Fig. 1 shows a video image before the background is removed. The man in the video who is speaking at some point turns his head to look toward screen left. Fig. 2 shows the same man in front of a new video background. VirtualU's edge sofetning tools ensure that the edges of the man are perfectly re-edged to the new video background. Other tools can also remove any existing edge softening.\par
     All testing has confirmed that the existing new code will do the job. Much work remains and it will be some time before the debut of this nice new tool. We have been involved in other projects and we are sorry that all of this has taken so long but we were always thinking about it and have dabbled with the code whenever possible. Our latest dabblings produced the breakthrough code solution. The remainder of the work to be done will be a no-brainer though time consuming and possibly tedious at times.\par
     The hard part is done.\par
     We have the code template and algorithms that will guide the rest of the work to be done. We are very excited about this outline tool. The intricate code elegantly mimics the human eyeball to operate in a simpler yet similar manner to detect the edges of foreground images.\par
     Other existing VirtualU manual tools will do the same job as the new outline tool but the new tool will make the whole process be much faster and easier since the program will do all or most of the work.\par
     We will be involved with other projects for the next three weeks or so but after that time period we hope to resume work on this new tool and then to continue this work for some time. We hope that this tool will be available sometime in February or March.\par
     We hope to finish by March since at that time our coder may encounter severe economic difficulties that would disrupt this task. We will see.\par
     Thank you and we will keep you advised.\par
