                                                                October 8, 2024\par
    A new version of VirtualU is available for download because changes, fixes and improvements were made and some new tools were added. This is a big one.\par
    *The tool "Image\\Change image color to solid color" uses a sample box that the user moves and positions. In previous versions when the Custom page was changed from a minimized state to a normal state after closing the Playback/Recording page, the sample box might be hidden behind a picture or video or text which could cause the user to not be aware of its existence. The program has been changed so that this box is always visible after using the Playback/Recording page.\par
    *We made extensive changes to the Custom page which is the main working page so that fewer restrictions will be placed on the order in which changes are made to pictures and videos. We were surprised at the number of changes required. We have been remiss but it's okay now.\par
    *We would like to resume work on Auto Outline System 2 but lately we have been finding other important things to do on VirtualU. These other things involve existing tools while the new partially completed new Outline tool is a future tool so the changes to existing tools take precedence. The focus on existing tools takes priority over a future tool since we will not allow a download version of VirtualU to contain known problems. The new Outline tool should get done eventually.\par
    *Improvement made: From now on, if a user tries to use any image-altering tool on a video which has a duration that is longer than the project duration then the program will tell the user that not all the frames of the video will be altered and will ask to continue or not. In many cases the user might have valid reasons for doing that but the alert message might prevent an error.\par
    *Change made: In previous versions, the program would on occasion ask the user to click on the background or foreground color of a video in order to do some processing. However, if the first frame of the video which shows on the Custom page did not contain that color then the user would be out of luck. If the user then loaded one of the frames which did contain the color, the program would reject the input because the sampled color did not come from the video as displayed on the Custom page. The program has been changed so that when prompted to input a color, the color chosen by the user can come from any source, not just the image being altered. This was done to make it easy and fast to input colors that may not be showing in the first frame.\par
    *Bug found: We were horrified to discover that the three unlock buttons on the locking page were not functioning correctly. This big unpleasant surprise has been fixed.\par
    *New Tool: By default the program always loads the first frame of all imported videos. A new tool called "Select And Show Frame From Imported Video" located in the Misc-Machines menu on the Custom page enables users to quickly load any frame extracted from a video into a separate and movable Custom page picture. This tool is useful when the user needs to imput a video frame color which does not show in the first frame. This tool is similar to "Image\\Switch sample image" but with some differences.\par
    *Improvement made: The Chart button process on the Locking page has been improved so that the information on the Chart page is more imformative.\par
    *Bug found: We discovered that if Method 8 in the Transparencies menu on the Custom page was used on a picture or video that was deleted before Method 8 was cancelled then the resulting program settings would be incorrect and the capture area might not be returned to its correct size and color. Not only that, in such a case the program would subsequently 'think' that Method 8 was still active. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *Improvements made: Improvements were made to the Method 4 manual edge softening system.\par
    *Improvement made to the image locking process: Let us say that image A is locked to the smaller image B and image B is on top of image A. In previous versions, if the user brings A to the top then B vanishes from view since it is smaller. The program has been changed so that in such a case as this, image B remains on top of image A after A is brought to the top.\par
    *New tool: The new item "Project\\Cancel recent "Move to top" w/explanation" on the Custom page allows the user to return all imports to their previous levels in the visual stack.\par
    *New tool: A new type of floodfill tool will be included in the next version of VirtualU and that new version will be available in a few days. This tool will fill interior areas of pictures and videos.\par
    We promise that the many changes that produced the current download version of VirtualU make operations on the Custom page much easier, faster and less confusing.\par
    The program may have some unknown minor idiosyncrasies but if so then we'll get 'em.\par
    The current download version of VirtualU contains the changes mentioned above.\par
\par
                                                             October 17, 2024\par
    A new version of VirtualU is available for download. This is another big one, even bigger than the previous upload.\par
    *New tool: The Outline page has a much needed new Skip button. In previous versions, the program would not allow the frame-by-frame processing mode to continue unless a change was made to every frame. The user now just presses the Skip button if no change is needed for a particular frame.\par
    *Improvements were made to the Method 4 manual edge softening system.\par
    *New tool: The Contrast/hue/lum/sat toolkit has a new playback tool to watch the loaded video. The Manual floodfill page also has the use of the playback tool.\par
    *Improvement made: A number of people have mentioned that VirtualU has too many forms (pages) so we considerably reduced the form count.\par
    *Program strengthened: For artistic reasons users may on occasion alter the PNG frames that VirtualU extracts from videos and we remembered that if this is done incorrectly then the program can crash when it tries to load a bad PNG. PNGs can be incorrectly saved in Paint. Thus, we have put all instances in which PNGs are loaded by VirtualU (such as in some recent code) into exception handlers that will prevent a crash.\par
    *New tool: A new tool called "Fill System 2 Manual Method" has been added to the "Contrast/hue/lum/sat" page toolkit.\par
