    *Changes were made to the "Contrast/hue/lum/sat" page to ensure that any particular action cannot proceed while some other action is pending. Other changes were made to ensure less confusion and more efficient operations.\par
    *New tool: A new tool called "Tools/Info\\Auto Vrs. Manual Floodfill Test" in the toolkit on the "Image\\Change contrast/hue/luminance/saturation" page can quickly tell the user if an Auto or Manual floodfill system is best to use on a video.\par
    *We deleted all log reports in this document the were reported prior to 2020 so that the size of this document would be smaller.\par
    The illustrations below shows what kind of floodfills the four current floodfill tools can do. There are 2 Auto fill methods and 2 Manual fill methods. The 2 Manual methods require the user to click on the areas to be filled, one frame at a time but a quick fingered user can manually process up to 240 frames in a minute.\par
    We have made numerous good changes to the program lately and we are pleased that they enhance VirtualU's capabilities. We have tested the program extensively but there's always the possibility that we missed some potential bug or idiosyncrasy. If so then any such problem will eventually surface and be discovered and then removed.\par
