    *New tool: The Check For Gaps button on the frame renumbering page has been changed to Find/Fix Gap/s. This updated tool will now both find and remove any gaps that exist in a numbered collection of frames.\par
    *New tool: The tool on the Contrast/hue/lum/sat (Color) page formerly listed as "Use Fill System 3 Manual Method" enabled the user to floodfill a solid color on a picture or video frame by clicking on that color. If a video was being altered then then the user would have to click on every frame. This tool has been upgraded to include an automatic mode so that now the user can alter all areas of the target color on every frame by clicking only once on the first frame.\par
    *New tool: The floodfill tool described above speeds up video processing but if the colored area that was clicked on in the first frame changed shape or moved around in subsequent frames then the colored area in those frames would not be filled if that area moved outside the point that was clicked on. This tool now has multiple options which enable the program to search for and fill in only that chosen colored area even if that area changes shape or moves away from the initial click point. The program tracks the movements of chosen areas.\par
    *Bug found: We discovered that when the Skip button on the System 2 and 3 floodfill video page was used then in many if not most cases the incorrect image whould appear on the Contrast/Color page when the floodfill page was closed. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *New tool: A new tool titled "Tools/Info\\Temporarily Load A Different Frame" on the Contrast/hue/lum/sat (Color) page enables the user to load a frame other than the first frame from which to get a sample color if the needed color sample is not visible in the first frame.\par
    *Minor bug found: The Custom page tool "Transparencies\\Get color sample" and possibly other tools would sometimes not work correctly if the format of an imported picture was something other than BMP. This bug has been fixed so that the color sample tool and other tools will work for all formats.\par
    *Improvements made: We took extensive steps to ensure that if any sub-program tool (contrast page, rotation page etc.) launched by the main program ever crashes or is terminated by the user then the main program will not be adversely affected.\par
    *Bug found: During testing, an image was altered on the Contrast/hue/lum/sat page but it was deleted before the change was applied with "Image\\Apply contrast/hue/lum/sat changes". When an attempt to import another image was subsequently made then the program erroroneously displayed a message that the alteration of the deleted image needed to be applied before any images could be imported. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *Improvements made: Many improvements were made to the Contrast/hue/lum/sat (Color) page which make operations easier and more understandable.\par
    *Bug fixed: When "Image\\Apply image color change" is selected on the Custom page to alter a video, the program makes a tentative change to the selected image. The program then allows the user to either apply the change to the frames or to cancel the tentative change. If the user cancels then the program is supposed to just remove that tentative change and do nothing else, regardless of whether any prior changes have been made by other tools. However, in previous versions if prior changes had been made when the cancellation is done then the program would erroneously remove all previous changes and get a new set of frames. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *New tool: The new tool "Misc-Machines\\Show The Name Of A Selected Import" enables the user to click on an image in order to see its file name. This can be useful if the user imports two files that have the same image or the same name.\par
    *Improvement made: VirtualU uses a queue system which keeps track of the order in which different tools are used on a picture or video so that the user may cancel a particular alteration without removing prior changes. The program has been improved so that now the user can choose between using or not using the queue system. Both options are useful.\par
    *Improvement made: The Queue system for pictures has been vastly changed so that all restrictions have been removed. Any tool may now be used on a picture or video at any time and in any order. \par
    *New tool: At long last the Method 4 edge softening process has a Cancel procedure. In previous versions the only way to cancel Method 4 was to delete the image and then re-import it or by first cancelling alterations which had been applied by other methods.\par
    *Improvement made: The menu item "Project\\Show active image altering methods" now shows the order in which each alteration tool is used. This active alterations page can now display the current and previous alteration sequence lists.\par
    *Tool removed: The tool "Remove edging from a one-color foreground image" in the Image menu on the Custom page has been removed. The other de-edging tool can do anything and more than the deleted tool could do so its presence was redundant.\par
    *Improvement made: The remaining De-Edging tool has been freed of all its constraints and linkages to the Rotation tool so that now the De-Edging tool can be used at any time and in the same way as the other image altering tools.\par
    *The edge softening page ("Image\\Edge softening - Method 1") has been improved to ensure that pictures are correctly handled.\par
    *New tool: The floodfill systems 2 and 3 page, launched by the contrast/hue/lum/sat (Color) page, now has a tool that enables the user to change the fill color without needing to return to the main Color page.\par
    *We checked VirtualU for memory leaks. There are no leaks.\par
    *Bug found and improvements made: The Custom page tool "Image\\Apply image color change" would sometimes completely wash out videos. This bug has been fixed. Steps were also taken to ensure that this process never crashes the program due to its memory array being exceeded. In the previous version this could happen if many different colors were taken in a single sampling. Out coder completely overhauled this tool and the way that it gathers information. The new system is more efficient, accurate, stable and faster. It can process up to 15,000 colors at a time. An unlimited number of colors can be sampled by making more passes on a picture or video. The memory block assigned to this tool is freed up after each pass.\par
    *Bug found: The tool "Special\\Ensure that video frames have 24-bits and correct format" on the Custom page would crash the program if it attempted to process extracted video frames which were misnamed, missing or misnumbered. An example of such a bad filename would be "image1 (2).png" instead of the correct name "image1.png". This bug has been fixed.\par
    *Improvement done: The Custom page tool "Image\\Apply edging" has been given crash protection against bad PNG files used by the program if they are corrupted outside of VirtualU.\par
    *Updating done: We proofread and updated the Tutorial, the Help files and all instructions.\par
    *We made numerous other minor improvements, much more than is shown here.\par
    We are very happy with the new floodfill tools. Users can do so much more now.\par
    VirtualU is a work in progress and it may contain quirks that we haven't found yet but we know of no current serious issues.\par
    Our coder has been working like a madman. Because of all the recent changes, we will continue to test this new version for a while even after it is uploaded to ensure that it has no problems. We will do this by making a new 30 minute video which will provide another shakedown of the program in order to root out any lurking quirks or bugs. This will delay the resumption of work on Auto Outline System 2, the tool that will enable users to lift out moving or still foreground images so that those images can be placed on and edge softened to different backgrounds. The delay should not be very long.\par
    The video will probably contain nice music, eye candy graphics and narration, all of which will visibly and audibly showcase what VirtualU can do.\par
    Note: Auto Outline System 2 is up and running though it's nowhere near ready so it is not yet available on the Outline page.\par
    We also will create a tool that softens areas of an image at the cursor point. The user will be able to adjust the range of the area to be softened as well as the amount of change to be applied.\par
    We will keep you advised.\par
    The current download version of VirtualU contains the changes mentioned above.\par
