                                                            June 13, 2025\par
A new version of VirtualU is available for download.\par
    *The biggest news is that the new video "VirtualU Tour 4" is ready and available now on YouTube. We made this video to promote the program and to shake it down. We did discover some good things and some bugs.\par
    *Improvement made: Some of the code that runs the cartoon process has been updated so that if a problem is encountered then the program will provide the user with quick and easy fixes.\par
    *Bug found: We discovered that when a video rotation was cancelled, the resulting erroneous image was incorrect or not visible. Misc-Machines\\Restore Video Image would display the correct image but this was still a bug that has been fixed.\par
    *Improvement made: During testing we found some problems in a third party open source audio editing program used by VirtualU called Audacity. This early version of Audacity was chosen because it is smaller than the newest version. If the frequency of a loaded audio file is changed and saved then the new file may have something wrong with it. Also, if two Audacity windows are open at the same time and extensive operations are done then both windows may suddenly close without warning. A new item in the Run menu on the Custom page mentions these problems and offers solutions.\par
    *Various improvements were made to the entire program, including some instances in the program needed to update things automatically.\par
    *Minor bug found: While using "Image\\Change image color to solid color" to alter a color in a video, the image that was showing we switched to one of the other frames. When an attempt was made to get a color sample from the switched frame, the image changed back to the original frame, preventing a sample to be taken from the switched frame. This problem has been fixed.\par
    *Improvement made: In previous versions, playbacks using MPlayer on the Playback/Recording page could only be done if a sound track was being used. MPlayer can now be used without sound tracks.\par
    *Improvement made: On the Playback/Recording page the Show Items button leads to the Audio Play/Rec. Options button which opens a settings page. On that settings page is a new Fast Forward tool which enables the user to play an external movie under construction from any chosen point in that movie. A user who only wants to look at a recent scene in a movie under construction does not have to play a long movie from its beginning.\par
    *Bug found: This problem wasn't actually a bug, it was a coding, logic error. The tool "Temporarily Load A Different Frame To Get A Color Sample" on the Contrast/hue/lum/sat (Color) page is supposed to enable the user to load some frame other than the first frame. When a test attempt was made to do that then the program erroneously said that the process was cancelled because the chosen frame was not the first frame. The whole point of this tool is to load a frame other than the first frame. This has been corrected.\par
    *New tool: The Playback/Recording page now has a simple fast forward tool for project playback when enables the user to save time when playback of the entire project duration is not needed. This tool and the fast forward tool for playback of an external movie under construction pretty much covers the waterfront.\par
    *The instructions, Help files and many other areas of the program have been updated and improved.\par
    *Bug found: We discovered that if the Esc key was pressed while no recording was being done on the Playback/Recording page then that page did not always return to its correct size and position. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *Improvement made: The settings page that appears when the Audio Play/Rec. Options button on the Playback/Recording page is pressed now includes more options for the playback of external movies that are under scene-by-scene construction.\par
    Future: Our coder wants to make a new zoom tool and another new tool that enables the user to soften specific areas of an image by moving the cursor over a picture or video but we'll see.\par
    The current download version of VirtualU contains the changes mentioned above.\par
