    *Improvement made: On some rare occasions the user might have artistic reasons for removing and altering the frames extracted from loaded videos. In previous versions if the user deleted even 1 frame from the set of frames extracted from a given video then it could cause the program to become "confused" and to issue confusing feedback to the user. The program has been altered so that it handles such cases better. (See the next item in this report.)\par
    *New tool: A new button called Restore Frames on the Film Options page replaces any frames that are removed by the user but not replaced.\par
    *Assorted improvements were made to VirtualU including the Tutorial.\par
    *Improvement made: Our coder made some changes to the Method 4 Auto edge softening tool which is now more reliable, efficient and faster.\par
    *Improvement made: The tool "Image\\Remove edging from a multi-color foreground image" on the Custom page has some new capabilities that enable it to properly handle Zoom 2 videos.\par
    *Big improvement made: In previous versions the tool Clean Interior in the Rotation page toolkit would only clean and soften transparencies, images with colored borders which can be clicked on and made to be transparent. This tool now softens all pictures and videos.\par
    No bugs were found. We will continue testing the new stuff and the program in general. We do not expect any problems with the new stuff.\par
