    A new version of VirtualU is available for download. Some improvements were made and some potential problems were fixed. We're sorry that we found these issues only after the previous version of VirtualU was made available but it's not always possible to be immediately anticipate all the effects that a new tool might produce. All errors are eventually fixed.\par
    *Bug found: The Restore Frames button on the Film Options page would sometimes erroneously report to the user that video frames were missing when in fact they were not. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *Big improvement: In previous versions when an attempt was made to apply edge softening to a video, the first attempt would usually fail and the user would be required to apply 10 points of contrast to the video before the edging page would do the edging. Such a situation was very inconvenient and it also would force the user to alter the image by applying contrast, something the user might not want to do. The edge softening page no longer requires the application of contrast before edging can be done. This problem has existed for a long time and it was only recently that our coder could fix it.\par
    *Bug found: This bug was very obscure and unlikely to occur but if it ever did then the results would be very serious. In previous versions, if the user for some reason physically removed all of the frames extracted from a video and then pressed the duration button on the Film Options page, a warning would be issued but also from that point on the duration and frame rate buttons would be disabled and useless. In a case like this, the only remedy would be to close and restart VirtualU. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *Improvements were made to the new zoom tool Zoomer 2.\par
    *Bug found: We discovered on the main edge softening page that the Status Of Current Edging page and the Frames ToDo box did not always display the correct number of frames to be processed. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *Improvement made: On the main edge softening page, the program would sometimes warn the user that the edging of the frames of a video must be done before the edging page is closed. The edging page has been altered so that this warning will appear less frequently, if at all.\par
