                                                              February 10, 2026\par
    A new version of VirtualU is available for download. Many improvements were made. \par
    *Improvements made: Updates and improvements have been done to the Help files, instructions, user prompts and infrastructure.\par
    *Improvement made: In previous versions the user would press the Demo button on the opening page to receive instructions to download, unzip and play a demo video. This download is no longer necessary because the program now provides a list of videos to view on YouTube. These videos show what VirtualU can do.\par
    *Problems found: The Custom page tool "Tools\\Show entire capture area" did not work correctly but it has been fixed. Playback on the Playback/Recording page did not function correctly when the capture area was set to the full screen disply size but it has been fixed.\par
    *Nice improvement made: The "Custom page\\Image\\Change contrast/hue/lum/sat" (Color) page now has a color spectrum illustration above the Hue trackbar scale pointer. As the pointer moves and displays the scale setting numbers, it also moves across the color spectrum so that the user can see what tints will be applied.\par
    *Huge improvement: The Film Options page is the main settings page. This page has been redesigned to better handle shutdowns of pending builds and builds in progress in an unconfusing way. The Restore Frames button has been removed because it is no longer needed. The program now automatically adjusts itself invisibly in all conditions and informs the user when something needs to be done. The program can also replace frames if the user removes extracted frames and then does not put them back. The program has the user's back and prevents errors.\par
    *Improvement made: The contrast/hue/lum/sat (Color) page has been altered so that now the user can move a large picture or video image to a location near the top of the Color page in order to see more of it. The user can now also hide some or all of the controls.\par
    *Bug found: We found this potentially bad bug in the Misc\\Record Fast Forward tool on the Playback/Recording page. The Fast Forward tool enables the user to begin the recording of a video at some frame other than the first frame of that video. We found during testing that this tool would sometimes malfunction, show error messages when no error occurred and sometimes it would even freeze the entire program. This tool has been fixed so that it now has no problems.\par
    *Improvements made: In addition to the fix described above, numerous improvements were made to the Record Fast Forward tool. For example, most limitations on the setting of the project duration have been removed. This page now has many more controls and options.\par
    *New tool: A video splicer is now available on the Playback/Recording page and it can be found on the same page as the Record Fast Forward tool (Misc\\Record Fast Forward). These two tools use some of the same code but they are used in different ways. This page now has a scale pointer that makes the work much easier. The Splicer tool grew out from the Fast Forward tool.\par
    *Improvement made: The tools "File\\Import picture file" and "File\\Import video" on the Custom page were improved.\par
    *New tool: A new tool installed on the Custom page will aid video splicing. This tool is named Incremental Speed Player and it enables the user to go back and forth through a video at any speed in order to determine the start and end frames for splicing operations. This tool is located in the Misc-Machines menu on the Custom page and also on the Fast Forward page.\par
    *Improvement made: In previous versions when a picture or video was imported, a brief flash would appear on the Custom page. The program has been changed so that this does not happen.\par
    *Bug found: The Esc key on the Playback/Recording page was supposed to stop a recording but we found that it no longer did that. This problem has been solved.\par
    *New tool: A new tool on the Incremental Speed Player page enables the user to determine the correct project duration for a splicing operation based on the positions of the start and end frames of the splice.\par
    *Improvement made and problems found: When the frames of an imported video are extracted, a progressbar appears with a box containing a countdown number. In previous versions the progressbar would sometimes act erratically and inaccurately. We also found that the number in the countdown box was not always accurate. These problems have been fixed.\par
    *Improvement made: VirtualU's video codecs have been tweaked so that videos loaded into the program more closely resemble the appearance of the original videos.\par
    *Problem fixed: In previous versions when a recording was made of the full size of the monitor display, some text would appear and show the percentage of how much of the processing was done. This text would not always be correct so now this text does not appear though a progressbar does appear so that the user can see how much processing remains to be done.\par
    *Improvement made: When a picture or video is imported into VirtualU, the image that appears on the Custom page is a "tentative" image, meaning that its first appearance does not always match exactly the original image. The program has been altered so that now when a video is imported and built into the project on the Film Options page, the image of the video showing on the Custom page is updated when the Film Options page is closed so that the image more closely resembles the original video.\par
    *Improvement made: We found that on the Playback/Recording page a playback would not always show all of a large image unless a recording was made first. This has been fixed. \par
    *Improvement made: In previous versions when a very large image was imported or when the capture size was changed to a very large size then the program would issue a reminder that recording times would take a while. This no longer happens, reducing the appearance of prompts.\par
    *Numerous changes were made to the program in order to strengthen it and prevent problems. \par
    *Improvement made: We redesigned and altered the process that extracts frames from loaded videos which vastly increased its speed, especially for videos with frame rates that divide evenly into the project duration.\par
    *Improvement made: The program will not do a build if an imported video has a higher frame rate than the current project frame rate. In cases like this the program now offers more options.\par
    Future plans: The program currently applies density codecs to imported videos but we plan to introduce new codecs that will adjust the color balance of imported videos so that they more closely resemble the original videos. For the time being, any color adjustments can be done on the Contrast/hue/lum/sat page.\par
    We also would like to introduce a new stretch tool on the Custom page that would enable the user to resize an image by dragging its edges. We plan to resume work on the half-finished Auto Outline System 2 tool when possible. This enables the user to lift foreground images out of a picture or video in order to place them onto new backgrounds.\par
    We are not satisfied with the way that the user must semi-sutomatically update VirtualU's screen capture settings every time that the computer's screen scale is changed. Our coder will soon resume work on an unrelated obligation which he and we are happy and pleased to do, but that work has not yet started so in the meantime we plan to do something about this and then to upload a new version very soon based on this one particular improvement, along with any corrections that may exist. In fact, we are working on it now.\par
    In summation, the program now has an improved Record Fast forward tool as well as a new video splicer. This is a nice dual purpose tool and it has many capabilities. It has been well tested and a picture of it is shown below. This tool is well worth the publication of a new version on its own merit. VirtualU actually now has two video splicers: The new splicer and the splicing capabilities of the Custom page menu item "Tools\\Extract frames from a video".\par
    After you extract the desired section of frames from a video with the latter tool, you then use "Tools\\Create movie from frames" to make a new video from that frame section.\par
    We will continue to test the program and to fix any problems as soon as they are found, if  any such problems appear. Our coder will be busy elsewhere for a while but we will continue to run and test the program to make sure that everything is okay. If a problem is found then our coder will temporarily disengage from what he is doing and fix it immediately.\par
    This report mentions some problems that were solved, which suggests the possibility that other unknown issues may exist though for the most part, any user is unlikely to encounter them and any such problems will most likely involve minor convenience issues.\par
    This new version is very nice and we are pleased with it. Thank you.\par
    The current download version of VirtualU contains the changes mentioned above.\par
