    *We also made a small change to the progressbar that appears when frames are being extracted. This change merely involved the frequency of how often the progressbar is displayed.\par
    *The page shown in the previous log report enables a user to splice a video or have a recording begin at some frame other than the first frame of that video. The settings are supposed to go into effect if the left checkbox is checked and all boxes of that video contain valid data. However, we discovered that if the user selected "Load Previous Settings" then the recording would erroneously not begin with the start frame as desired unless a right click was done on a video's number box. This has been fixed.\par
    *In the previous log report we said that we were not satisfied with the way that the user must update VirtualU's settings every time that the screen display scale is changed but research, study and available code indicates that the current updating system is the best answer. It is failsafe and it should work on all monitors, regardless of their own differences and peculiarities which are many. For example, the far left edge on some monitors is indicated to be zero when in fact the actual number is a negative number.\par
    We uploaded without fanfare the corrected version which is the current download version.    \par
    Other than these changes, the current download version is the same as the Feb. 10 version.\par
    We will keep you advised.\par
