\pard\sl240\slmult1                                                                 May 4, 2026\par
    A new version of VirtualU is available for download. Many improvements were made and some new stuff was added to the program. We were surprised at the number of bugs that were found but at least they have been fixed.\par
    *Bad bug found: To our complete and shocking surprise, we discovered that the Playback/Recording page was not recording smaller capture sizes correctly. This bug has been fixed and this page works fine now.\par
    *Improvement made: The softening tool in the Rotation page toolkit has been improved.\par
    *Improvement made: The instructions and help information on the Method 4 Auto edge softening settings page have been updated and improved. New help info has been added.\par
    *Possible bug found: We're not sure if the Method 4 Manual edge softening page was malfunctioning in previous versions but we did have some problems with it. In any event the problems have been fixed and improvements have been made as shown later in this text.\par
    *Improvement made: The Queue system for pictures has been improved. The Queue system for pictures enables alterations to be cancelled without removing prior alterations.\par
    *Problem found: When VirtualU is run, one of the first things that it does is to get information about the display monitor. In all the history of VirtualU, this process has never failed except on one occasion. We have changed and strengthened this process so that it never fails. The program has been changed so that in the unlikely event that it does fail, the user will be prompted to manually input the display resolution sizes.\par
    *Improvement made: When the Audio Play/Rec. Options button on the Playback/Recording page is pressed, a page titled "Audio Playback And Recording Options" will appear. The wording of the movie options has been changed to lessen confusion.\par
    *Bug found: Method 8 in the Transparencies menu on the Custom page would not always cancel correctly. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *Improvement made: The edge softening page has a new menu item titled "Basics\\Getting Started And Avoiding Confusion". This menu item displays a tutorial which includes step by step instructions on how to use the edge softening page and the Method 4 edging system.\par
    *Bug found: We discovered that the main edge softening page tool Special Internal Edge Softening System 2 was not working correctly. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *Improvements made: The user prompts, information and instructions have been updated.\par
    *Bug found: We found that on some occasions after edge softening done on a video was cancelled, some parts of the program would still erroneously 'think' that the edging had not been cancelled. This bug has been fixed.\par
    *Big improvement made: On the Method 4 Manual Edge Softening page, multiple colors on pictures can now be selected in the same session so that the edges of all those colors can be softened at the same time. This speeds up the whole process. This cannot be done with videos on the Method 4 Manual page but it can be done with the Method 4 Auto Edge Softening system.\par
    *On some very rare occasions the Film Options button on the Custom page would fail to load the Film Options page and it would then only work if VirtualU was shut down and then restarted. Changes have been made to prevent this from happening again.\par
    Bugs found: Testing showed that the Method 4 Auto Edge Softening system on the Playback/Recording page was only working correctly part of the time. These bugs have been fixed and this system is working fine. The quality of the edging has been improved.\par
    *Improvement made: The speed of the Special Internal Edging System 2 on the main edge softening page has been increased.\par
    *Bug found: The Method 4 Manual edge softening page is used to further improve the edging done on the main edge softening page. When a video is edged with the Method 4 Manual page, a series of tracings is created to guide the edging process. We found that in some cases the program would erroneously delete those tracings before they could be used. This has been fixed.\par
    *Improvement made: The main edge softening page has been improved and updated.\par
    The current download version of VirtualU contains the changes listed above.\par
\par
                                                                  May 9, 2026\par
    A new version of VirtualU is available for download.\par
    *New tool: A new tool titled "Problems And Fixes\\Remove Last Scene From MPG Being Built" is now available on the Playback/Recording page. This tool is useful if the last recorded scene in an external movie is incorrect for some reason. For example, we have found that in very rare cases a recorded MPG may be all black. This can happen because of the capture area size or the size dimensions of an imported picture or video.\par
    *Changes made: The tool "Misc-Machines\\Lock Or Unlock Text And/Or Images Together" on the Custom page has been working fine but the wording on some of the buttons on that page was a bit confusing. That wording has been changed so that this tool is more understandable.\par
    *The process that gets information on the display monitor when VirtualU is started has been improved so that it is more reliable.\par
    *New tool: A new tool titled "Misc.\\Show The Current No. Of Scenes In The Movie Being Built" on the Playback/Recording page displays the existing number of scenes in an external movie being built.\par
    *Improvements have been made to Help files, user prompts, information and instructions.\par
    *The Playback/Recording page has new options and menu items.\par
    *Improvements were made to the Edge Softening page, the softening tool in the Rotation page toolkit and to the Queue system for pictures.\par
    No bugs were found.\par
    We continue to test and develop VirtualU by making videos, the former to provide users with a useful program and the latter to provide them with something nice to play..\par
    The play is the thing. - William Shakespeare\par
    The current download version of VirtualU contains the changes listed above.\par
